data.enText: saying or doing sth that you do not really mean or believe

example: a charming but thoroughly insincere woman
their praise was extravagant and insincere

value.def: If you say that someone is insincere, you are being critical of them because they say things they do not really mean, usually pleasant, admiring, or encouraging things.

example.ex: Some people are so terribly insincere you can never tell if they are telling the truth...
example.tran: 有些人非常虚伪,你根本说不准他们是否在讲实话。

example.ex: John found himself surrounded by insincere flattery.
example.tran: 约翰发现自己为虚情假意的奉承阿谀所包围。

example.ex: Too many superlatives lend a note of insincerity.
example.tran: 太多的“最如何如何”让人觉得不够真诚。
